## Plesk for Linux

- Login to server as root via SSH
- Download the Auto-installer utility that suits your operating system from http://sp.parallels.com/products/plesk/download/ and save it on your server's hard drive. At the moment the latest version is Plesk 12
- Download auto-installer to your server /usr/local/src and set executive permission for auto-installer

```
cd /usr/local/src/
wget http://autoinstall.plesk.com/plesk-installer
```

- Run the auto-installer. To install older versions such as Plesk 11, the auto-installer must be run with the ‘--**all-versions**’ parameter.

```
sh ./plesk-installer
```
